Parliament, Tuesday, 4 September 2018 – The Joint Standing Committee on Financial Management of Parliament today elected Dr Mathole Motshekga as one of its Co-Chairpersons. Dr Motshekga filled the vacancy that was left by Mr Vincent Smith, who has been redeployed to another parliamentary committee. In accepting the new responsibility, Dr Motshekga said: “Holding Parliament accountable cannot be a party political matter. We will all have to put aside our political differences, put the interests of the people of South Africa above and ensure that Parliament remains a truly people’s Parliament.” ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CO-CHAIRPERSONS OF THE JOINT STANDING COMMITTEE ON FINANCIAL MANAGEMENT OF PARLIAMENT, MR MOTALANE MONAKEDI AND DR MATHOLE MOTSHEKGA. For media enquiries, please contact the committee’s Media Officer: Name: Mr Mava Lukani
